<p>
  <span class="nym">Alard</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Old English</span> <i>æþel</i>, <span class="lang">Old High German</span> <i>adal</i> 'noble' + <span class="lang">Old English</span> <i>heard</i>, <span class="lang">Old Saxon</span> <i>hard</i>, <span class="lang">Old High German</span> <i>hart</i> 'strong, hard'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a 9th C French saint and cousin of Charlemagne.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The German vernacular form <i>Adilhart</i> is witnessed c1100 in the place name <i>Adilhartsdorf</i> (<span class="bibl"><span class="key">UrkStyr</span> <span class="loc">89</span></span>).</p>
  
  


